gomodel:SYNGO_5022  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" , "Rationale: Figure 3: vti1a is localized to small synaptic vesicles in the mossy fiber nerve terminals by immuno-electron microscopy. While labeling at the synapse was abundant, vti1a was also found in high abundance at Golgi and TGN (Figure 2)\n\nFigure 6: vti1a is enriched in biochemical preparations enriched in synaptic vesicles.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M, section on EM: \"Adult rat brain was isolated after transcardial perfusion with 4% paraformaldehyde, cut into 200-m slices using a vibratome, and blocks containing the mossy fiber area were cut out.\"\n\nno clear specification of the antibody used for EM, but probably the same as used in previous paper by same authors; PMID:10908612" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5022" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

